Welcome to July's Turing-Roche newsletter! We hope you are having a nice summer so far. Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute, Roche and beyond.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FMhjPzX9vzDLsJ5lsP0OyDQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727690764759%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=CONNPUh5lruxZPHu5jPl5K12c%2F912xuqYDIWZY323Ew%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FBc3SVfEYeXzggpoJ4RYGjA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727690764759%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=6liNhM1d%2B6Vj2l1RAvauZEqlM5cMr3Bj9oMMcQifNWw%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FTBu1UWA0pywo9VNsPj9cGQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727690764759%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=p96F0nHudIRSd%2BQZGGquiYg9oi3XGV6prTbNuXAZGwY%3D&reserved=0).

### Apply for the Partnership Community Scholar Scheme

**Deadline for applications: 31 July 2023**

Applications remain open till the 31st July for our Turing-Roche Community Scholar scheme. This year-long scheme open to PhD students will award up to 10 successful applicants a stipend of £3000 to embed themselves within our partnership, attend a relevant conference and undertake a selected, community based project. Scheme info and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FCFehZBftQy0icd-EE0Wbcw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727690764759%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=2rls%2FUJDnH%2BK5XTNzxeVrNsnf7Y5Ue3xA%2FTRl%2BZ5XIE%3D&reserved=0).

### Next Turing Lecture Series Announced

The Turing Institute's flagship lecture series is set to return for a second year and will focus on key issues relating to the emerging fields of generative AI and large-language models (LLMs). The series, commencing on the 22nd September, will feature three leading researchers considering the impact of these technologies on different areas of society. They will explore the risks and benefits of these technologies, dispel myths and drive the public conversation on this divisive topic. Find out more and how to register [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FwUL9auK1n7dE58j_YimjtA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727690921026%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ssJ%2BH4Pc22SVDp0ZdJZt%2Borl7zXYBuYGuLsYRMb%2BXHI%3D&reserved=0).

### AI and Data Science in Multi-Omics for Human Health Workshop at Northumbria University

**27-28 July 2023**

Northumbria University are hosting a two-day networking workshop to find out more about ongoing progress, open opportunities, and challenges pertinent to AI Biomedicine and data science approachs in multi-omics for human diseases. It will bring together researchers and professionals who leverage AI and data science in biomedical, omics, clinical, bio-industries, and computer sciences sectors. More info and registration details [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FhrgNsB6gRIXxXmBfK7roGw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727690921026%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Ep5rsdpta8KhdoVTDDdy4NFg553lD1c9q3oY%2FI5bMA8%3D&reserved=0).

### Three researcher positions open at the Ada Lovelace Institute

**Deadline 19 July 2023**

The Ada Lovelace Institute is hiring for 3 researchers to support their research on the impacts of AI and data on society. These 2 year fixed term contract positions will work with senior researchers and other team members to design, deliver, and support the impact of Ada's projects across three research domains: society, justice and public sector, emerging technology and industry practice and law and regulation. Find out more and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FaGbE3U_X0BxJQTw-U3dtPQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727691077299%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=boGsZqj8ZpOwAOHV%2BhB8DiV%2FRmr9%2B%2BPGmI9l9OpSV7s%3D&reserved=0).

## Publication of the Month

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/patrick-tomasso-oaqk7qqnh_c-unsplash2.jpg)

### Deep-Fuzz: A synergistic integration of deep learning and fuzzy water flows for fine-grained nuclei segmentation in digital pathology

July's publication of the month is from our partnership senior postdoctoral research associate Rohan Chakraborty and his collaborators. Published in PLOS One, the [paper](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_%2Fs7z1YdBRRcdeHMwtsEgobA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2431d70c84e74c1d975b08db87796110%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638252727691077299%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=cxMSu8gZd073vRnSxW2EeYjGmqXlKLrg%2F0lkqU23uww%3D&reserved=0) presents a 'hybrid deep learning' pipeline that integrates a data driven deep learning model with an interpretable mechanistic model for robust segmentation of cell nuclei from tumour microenvironment in digital pathology.
